{{Expand French|Alexandre Corréard|date=January 2012}}
'''Alexandre Corréard''' (8 October 1788 – 16 February 1857) was a [[France|French]] engineer and geographer. He graduated from the engineering school [[Arts et Métiers ParisTech]].
He is famous for escaping  "[[The Raft of the Medusa]]" shipwreck and collaborating with [[Géricault]] when he was painting his famous masterpiece.

