{{Unreferenced|date=November 2010}}
The {{nihongo|'''Kumano Region'''|熊野地方|Kumano chihō}} is a region situated on the southern part of the [[Kii Peninsula]] in Japan, former [[Muro District, Kii|Muro District]]. It includes parts of [[Mie Prefecture]], [[Wakayama Prefecture]], and [[Nara Prefecture]].

In 2004 it became a [[UNESCO]] designated [[World Heritage Site]].

